Splitscreen (version 1.0)
(C) Francois Dechelle 2010

A simple library for terminal output, that allows to display
output and read input in separated areas, using curses library.


Prerequisites
=============

The curses library must be installed, both runtime and development
files. This can be done on Ubuntu 12.04 with:
$ sudo apt-get install libncurses5-dev


Compilation
===========

To compile, just run 'make'


Tests and examples
==================

There are 2 tests provided with the sources, that are also 
programming examples:
- test1: simple input/output
- test2: input/output using select()


Functions
=========

See documentation in splitscreen.h

void splitscreen_init( int nlines, const char *prompt)
void splitscreen_prompt(void)
int splitscreen_input_char( void)
int splitscreen_input_line( char *buf, int size)
void splitscreen_output( const char *buf)
void splitscreen_quit( void)



